history.text: Hi!
Hi!
We're going to talk about Batman Vs. Superman.
Awesome! I'm a total nerd. What is the rating on that movie?
Did you see it? I had no idea it scored this low on Rotten Tomatoes.
27% that's really low
Hahaha. That is pretty bad. It's because it's so dark I think
It did better on Meta Critic 44%
It also was awful except in the scenes with Wonder Woman.
Lol. Why is that?
Well, Batman's motivations made him sound like a hysterical bigot. Luthor was totally wrong characterization, WW was the one most true to her character.
Well that makes sense. I was really hoping Ben Affleck would be a popular Batman though :(
I think the critics are a little harsh, but it wasn't worth the time.
How was Superman's performance?
I didn't really have a problem with Affleck. Jesse Eisenstein though...
Jesse Eisenburg is good  at comedy. And he is good with a strong lead.
I like Amy Adams, but she just didn't fit as Lois either.
Normally, he's very good. But the script here made him more bonkers, and less calculating.
True. So we are blaming the script writers? I wonder who wrote it
Does a score this low put you off or make you want to see for yourself?
Eh. I never trust critics so I would watch it anyway
I just wouldn't take my son until I've screened it first
They were actually right on about 90% of the criticism
I think it was a bit dark for kids.
Though I did like one thing a lot. They address the massive destruction in Man Of Steel
That's what I'm thinking. I always screen dc movies first because they are dark. I let him watch wonder woman though
It's the one valid reason Batman has for thinking Superman was dangerous.
I never even thought about that. Hmm
So Batman goes off the deep end over superman messily saving the world?
It's a weak premise
That was the thing the critics pointed out. The level of destruction during the battle killed people in those buildings.
He does. And the bigotry angle of "What does this alien want here?"
I'd say it's better than the whole city dying...
Exactly, thought a later in his career Superman would have found a way to draw Zod away from the city
In B vs S they purposely take the battle to an abandoned area
Right.
Does Batman become less hated as the movie goes on or is he just a jerk the whole time?
He gets better when he meets Supse mam
And the most laughable thing-when he finds out their mothers had the same name.
Hahaha auto correct. Mine kept changing superman to Sherman
ha
Lol. I actually didn't catch that part. Maybe I fell asleep.
haha
Yeah, it actually made everyone laugh when I saw it.
It was so strange. They played it like Batman snapped out of a trance.
Yep. Must have fallen asleep. I did see it in Palm springs  ca though so it was mostly older people
That is weird. Weak premise and weak resolve I suppose

I'm in NYC. We go
 at all times here
It was shockingly bad.
Ah!! Jealous. Now that I'm back east I'm finally going up to NYC this thanksgiving
Nice. Get there early for the parade. They set up barrier the night before.
Well, I think we hit all the points.
It was nice talking to you!
Great! Pleasure chatting!

uid2response.feedback: Well originally I would say I'd go no matter what. But the more I heard about the characters and reviews it just doesn't sound good.
